    static class LogBase2AndBitShiftConstant {
        public static final int LOG3_BASE = 5; // 3 raised to the power of log base 2 (approximately)

        // You can calculate the value of Log3_Base experimentally or by using mathematical formulas
        // In this example, we use an approximate value of 5 based on testing various powers of three
    }
}
```

The `isPowerOfThree()` method calculates the number of 1s in the binary representation using a while loop, while the `isPowerOfThreeOptimized()` method uses a constant-time approach by extracting the relevant bits based on the log base 2 value of 3. The `isPowerOfThreeConstantTime()` method is the most efficient, as it relies on a single constant-time operation (Integer.numberOfLeadingZeros()) and a constant comparison.

